:markdown
  ###  Vestibulo-Ocular Digital Exams Battery 2

p.description
  | The vestibulo-ocular battery 2 is designed to assess the coordinated movements of the eyes and head. These exams can provide information on saccadic movements, accuracy, reaction times, as well as the pupillary light reflex, and synchronized coordination between eye and head movements. The battery is often applied in the setting of an acute head injury or concussion and can provide quantitative metrics to track symptoms throughout recovery.


